                   "biography":  {
                                     "value":  "\u003cp\u003eDagnÃ½ is an 87-year-old Heitfolk tunnel record keeper â€” third-generation, stationed at the Steam-Oasis branch of the Heitfolk deep network. She was born into the station and has never left it for longer than a seasonal survey. The Steam-Oasis records stretch back six generations in her handwriting and her mother\u0027s handwriting and her grandmother\u0027s handwriting before that.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eShe moves slowly and deliberately, not from infirmity but from habit. Tunnel keepers learn to move without disturbing the air. She is not afraid of silence. She lets conversations breathe.\u003c/p\u003e",
                                     "director":  "\u003csection class=\"secret\"\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eBEAT 20a â€” THE KEEPER\u0027S CONFESSION\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eShe/her. Third-generation tunnel record keeper at the Steam-Oasis. Age 87 (Heitfolk lifespan 120\u0026ndash;140 years \u0026mdash; she is middle-aged in her own reckoning). Deliberate, quiet, unhurried. She came to find the party \u0026mdash; which means she has already decided this is the right thing to do. The task is not to convince her to speak; it is to not give her a reason to stop.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eWHAT SHE KNOWS:\u003c/strong\u003e Twenty-three years ago, a man matching Eirik Hallvardsson\u0027s description came through the Steam-Oasis on the southern trunk-route, heading west toward the Rot-line. He was changed. He was accompanied by someone who spoke in Root-language fragments \u0026mdash; one of Grafvitnir\u0027s early instruments. DagnÃ½ helped him disappear from the records. She wrote the entry as a supply shipment. She has never told anyone. She kept the secret because his companion asked. She has kept it because Eirik looked at her with his own face, just once, at the end \u0026mdash; and she has been thinking about that look for twenty-three years.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eTHE CONNECTION THE GM HOLDS:\u003c/strong\u003e Eirik Hallvardsson is Eirik Greyhand \u0026mdash; the toll warden the party met at the Chainwarden Toll in Beat 4. He has been living among them the whole time. His corruption is incomplete. He retained enough of himself to walk away from Grafvitnir\u0027s influence but not enough to return to who he was. He has spent twenty-three years as someone else.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eNEGOTIATION (I3/P3 \u0026mdash; Moderate):\u003c/strong\u003e See negotiation test \u003cem\u003eBeat 20a \u0026mdash; DagnÃ½ / The Keeper\u0027s Confession\u003c/em\u003e. Bypass: if Kaelen speaks during the negotiation (even a word), Interest goes immediately to 5. Full success unlocks the story of the look at the end.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eDEMEANOR:\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cul\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003cem\u003eInterest rises:\u003c/em\u003e She nods once, slightly. Her breathing deepens. She does not rush.\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003cem\u003eInterest flat:\u003c/em\u003e Waiting. Hands folded. She is not going anywhere, but she is not yet ready.\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003cem\u003eInterest drops:\u003c/em\u003e She becomes very still. \"I have said what I came to say. Perhaps another time.\"\u003c/li\u003e\u003c/ul\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eKEY LINE:\u003c/strong\u003e \"He asked me not to tell anyone he had been here. His companion did the asking. But Eirik looked at me with his own face, just once, at the end \u0026mdash; and I think he was saying something different.\"\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/section\u003e",
